{
  "texts": [
    "From attention weights A ∈ R B×H×N ×N, we compute: (1) the rowstochastic transition matrix P by averaging across heads and normalizing, (2) its stationary distribution π via power iteration on P ⊤, (3) the Attention Consensus Index",
    "where Π = diag(π) and σ 2 (•) is the second-largest singular value of the Π-symmetrized chain, measuring global mixing rate, and (4) the CLS Centrality CCC = π 0 quantifying hub importance.",
    "Higher ACI indicates faster information propagation; lower CCC indicates hub marginalization.",
    "All three models exhibit progressive [CLS] marginalization but with different outcomes.",
    "ViT-S reduces CCC from 0.458 to 0.018 (96.1%), ViT-B from 0.502 to 0.004 (99.3%), and ViT-L from 0.373 to 0.010 (97.2%)."
  ]
}